Transcribing and Structuring Medical ConversationsAmazon Transcribe Medical is purpose-built for high-accuracy medical speech-to-text. It handles complex medical terminology, accents, and speaker diarization.Example: Using AWS CLI for a batch transcription job (for retrospective analysis)aws transcribe start-medical-transcription-job \
    --medical-transcription-job-name "clinical_interview_001" \
    --language-code "en-US" \
    --media-format "mp3" \
    --media-sample-rate-hertz 16000 \
    --output-bucket-name "your-raw-transcripts-bucket" \
    --output-key "transcriptions/clinical_interview_001.json" \
    --medical-content-category "MEDICAL_RECORDING" \
    --specialty "PRIMARYCARE" \
    --type "CONVERSATION" \
    --media "s3://your-audio-source-bucket/clinical_interview_001.mp3" \
    --settings '{"ShowSpeakerLabels": true, "MaxSpeakerLabels": 2}'
